author: SomeOrdinaryGamers
description:
Hello guys and gals, it's me Mutahar again! This time we take a look at Google and their recent behaviour regarding a small project that powers the very video you're watching. Google recently disclosed several problems in regards to safety when it comes to FFmpeg, now it expects people to do the work for free that they should be doing. Thanks for watching!

title: Google Is In The Wrong For This...
